* Testbench for MoTe2 Phase Change Memristor (Alpha Parameter Model)

* Load the new alpha-based Verilog-A module
.verilog "A_Mem_Code_Alpha.va"

* Drive with a 4.0V sine wave at 1 kHz (matches the Python script)
V1 p 0 SIN(0 4.0 1000)

* Instantiate the Phase Change device
YVLG1 p 0 w_monitor A_Mem_Code_Alpha
Rmon w_monitor 0 1G

* Analysis Setup
* Run for exactly 1 cycle (1 millisecond). 
* Using a tiny 100ns step to capture the violent Arrhenius exponential snaps perfectly.
.tran 100n 1m

* Export waveforms for SmartView
.plot v(p) i(YVLG1.p)
.end